Depends: zfsutils-linux, coreutils, util-linux, {{ DEPS }}
Description: persist the Proxmox VE cluster config (pmxcfs) on a ZFS dataset
 The pmxcfs database (/var/lib/pve-cluster/config.db, which backs /etc/pve) holds
 the node's Proxmox VE configuration. On the single OS disk (btrfs) it is lost if
 that disk dies or is reinstalled. This tool relocates it onto a ZFS dataset — on
 redundant data storage that the installer never touches — and re-mounts it there
 before pve-cluster starts, so the configuration survives disk failure and OS
 reinstalls.
 .
 Opt-in: set the target dataset in /etc/dc-config-zfs/dc-config-zfs.conf (empty by
 default = disabled, the service is then a no-op).
